NAME
        format_idle_time - converts a time integer into a string.
		
SYNOPSIS
        string format_idle_time(int time)

DESCRIPTION
        Converts a time integer into a string.  The string is in form of 
	xy, where x is int and y is a unit of time.  The unit in y is the 
	largest unit formed, the number in x the number of whole units 
	formed.  Example: idle for 6 hours 20 minutes -> 6h.
		
RETURN VALUE
        Returns a string expressing an elapsed amount of time.

SEE ALSO
	afun/format_time

